Defendant Lornell Washington in court with attorney Anne M. Jaspers.  Defendant Lornell Washington in custody.  Megan Patricia Carmody appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Count 2, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 4 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  6 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Count 1, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 3 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING 2 1/2 YEARS OF THESE SENTENCES.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victim M.H. (d.o.b. 8/03/2001);
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given.
